        <iri>
          <value>http://cdm.ovh/rsm/operations/rope</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/taf/tafp5#</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>In the context of operations in general, and the TAF TSI in particular, "weight"  is often used instead of "mass" while the latter is correct (and units are indeed mass units, e.g. kg). In the present ontology, we only use "mass"  in identifiers and labels.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
